OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FHelp house 10,000 Afghans, 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fminister tells councils    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The refugees minister has appealed to  
OL,6, councils to help house 10,500 Afghans  
OL,7, currently living in UK hotels at a cost
OL,8, to the taxpayer of #1m a day.          
OL,10,FLord Harrington told councils the      
OL,11,Fgovernment had fewer than 100          
OL,12,Fproperties available in June, but      
OL,13,Fexpects 500 Afghan arrivals each month.
OL,15,FSeveral Afghans said living in hotels  
OL,16,Fhad left them unable to settle.        
OL,18,F"I know this is costing the British    
OL,19,Fpeople but for what?" one refugee told 
OL,20,FBBC Two's Newsnight.                   
